Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve and peel the @onion{2}. Cut each half into 2cm wedges.

Place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the @Diced Irish Chicken Breast{260%grams} and onion.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging we use to keep it fresh.

Fry the onion and chicken, stirring occasionally, until the chicken is golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

With ~{1%minute} left to cook, add the @Middle Eastern Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} to the pan.

Remove from the heat and stir in the @Yoghurt{75%grams} and @Green Pesto{1%sachet}.

Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Meanwhile, trim and quarter the @Radish{125%grams}.

Cut the @Tomato{2} into 2cm chunks.

In a #salad bowl{}, mix the tomato and radish with a drizzle of oil, @salt{1/2%tsp} and pepper.

Just before serving, add the @Salad Leaves{40%grams} to the bowl and toss to combine.

Place @Naan{2} onto a #baking tray{}. Sprinkle with a little @Water{to taste} and pop them into the oven to warm, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Top the warm naans with your radish salad and pesto chicken.

Finish with a drizzle of @Balsamic Glaze{2%sachets}.